42.jpg?v=1651599001 1536w" width="1152" height="768" alt="woman holding a black diffuser" title="What is a diffuser?"/></div><p class="sc-fmBCVi laenLa pf-63_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jtXEFf kGfXVs pf-65_">Dating back as far as the first century, essential oils have been enjoyed for their unique abilities and healing properties, both mentally and physically. Greek physicians and botanists wrote about the positive impact of essential oils on the human body and noted that most of these benefits can be enjoyed by simply <a href="/blogs/guides/are-oil-diffusers-safe-for-the-lungs" target="_self">inhaling the aromas</a>.
<br><br>In the past, evaporation was the main method used to disperse essential oils around the home. Luckily, modern technology has stepped in, creating the modern day diffuser that people across the globe have grown to love.
<br><br><a href="/blogs/guides/best-affordable-diffusers" target="_self">Diffusers are an easy and efficient way to transform your space and make your home smell great</a>. They work by dispersing tiny molecules of essential oils into the air, allowing the aroma of the oils to quickly fill the air. This enables essential oils to be distributed quickly and consistently into the air at a pace which is best suited to you. <a href="/blogs/guides/heat-vs-ultrasonic-essential-oil-diffusers" target="_self">Most modern electric essential oil diffusers use ultrasonic technology</a>, or quickly vibrating sound waves we can’t hear, to vaporize the water and oils.<br><br>Electric diffusers are quick and easy to use, enabling essential oils to seamlessly become part of your daily routine. This enables you to enjoy that ‘just cleaned’ feeling in your home every single day, whilst rejuvenating both your body and mind at the same time.
<br><br><a href="/blogs/guides/how-do-essential-oil-diffusers-work" target="_self">To use an electric diffuser</a>, simply fill the container with water to the fill line and add 20-25 drops of your chosen essential oil. Then, replace the plastic lid and stone cover, select whether you prefer a continuous stream or intervals and you’re ready to go. Your diffuser will then do the rest for you whilst you go about your everyday life, inhaling the beneficial aromas of essential oils.
