on" class="sc-bQtKYq fbyRgD pf-82_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-jHkVzv dyVEVs"><div class="sc-hiCibw hHrFfF pf-83_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hAcGzb bAQARH pf-84_"><div class="sc-hiCibw hHrFfF pf-85_ pf-r pf-c-cm" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hAcGzb bAQARH pf-86_"><div class="sc-hiCibw hHrFfF pf-87_ pf-r pf-c-cm" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hAcGzb bAQARH pf-88_"><div class="sc-hiCibw hHrFfF pf-89_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hAcGzb bAQARH pf-90_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-ctqQKy ioCblW pf-91_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jtXEFf kGfXVs pf-93_">Create your own DIY diffuser at home</span></h3><div title="Create your own DIY diffuser at home" data-pf-type="Image" class="sc-evcjhq dAUdgU pf-94_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0535/9088/4510/t/3/assets/reed-diffuser-1651599772396.jpg?v=1651599775" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0535/9088/4510/t/3/assets/reed-diffuser-1651599772396.jpg?v=1651599775 1536w" width="2245" height="1587" alt="Reed Essential Oil Diffuser" title="Create your own DIY diffuser at home"/></div><p class="sc-fmBCVi laenLa pf-95_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jtXEFf kGfXVs pf-97_">If you’re new to the exciting world of essential oils, you might be looking for a quick solution to help you use your essential oils, whilst you order a diffuser. Panic not, reed diffusers are quick and easy to make, with materials most people have laying around the house!<br><br>An old jam jar is perfect to get you started, or you could even use an empty perfume bottle. The jar or bottle will need a small opening at the top. If your jar has a cork lid, you can create this opening using a drill. It’s useful to note that the smaller the opening is, the slower your essential oils will evaporate, and the longer they will last.<br><br>Once you’ve got your container ready, add about a quarter of a cup of carrier oil to your container, along with a dash of alcohol to help bind the products together. Vodka or rubbing alcohol work best for this. The <a href="/collections/carrier-oils" target="_self">carrier oil</a> that you choose should be light in consistency to enable effective diffusion. Sweet almond oil is our favourite! However, fractionated coconut oil lasts a long time without going rancid.
<br><br>Then comes the exciting part: add 25-30 drops of your favourite essential oils. You can choose one oil or try combining several different oils together to create the perfect blend for your space.
<br><br>When the mixture is ready, place some reed sticks into the solution. Reeds that are made from rattan work best for this, thanks to their small vertical channels. These channels allow the oil to travel upwards and diffuse effectively into the air. You can purchase rattan reeds in large quantities online, from websites such as Amazon.
<br><br>If you don’t have rattan reeds handy or don’t want to wait for them, you can use bamboo sticks or skewers in a pinch. These won’t work as well, but it’s a start. You could also try using other sticks and stems you find around. <br><br>&nbsp;You can then enjoy inhaling the aromas from your homemade reed diffuser, as the scent of the essential oils slowly disperse through your home. When the diffuser becomes empty, simply refill the container and replace the reeds. (Although if the oil has gone rancid, you’ll need to wash it out first.)
</span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-3093" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-bQtKYq fbyRgD pf-98_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-jHkVzv dyVEVs"><div class="sc-hiCibw hHrFfF pf-99_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hAcGzb bAQARH pf-100_"><div class="sc-hiCibw hHrFfF pf-101_ pf-r pf-c-cm" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hAcGzb bAQARH pf-102_"><div class="sc-hiCibw hHrFfF pf-103_ pf-r pf-c-cm" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hAcGzb bAQARH pf-104_"><div class="sc-hiCibw hHrFfF pf-105_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hAcGzb bAQARH pf-106_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-ctqQKy ioCblW pf-107_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jtXEFf kGfXVs pf-109_">Mug warmer or candle warmer</span></h3><div title="Mug warmer or candle warmer" data-pf-type="Image" class="sc-evcjhq dAUdgU pf-110_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0535/9088/4510/t/3/assets/use-heat-diffuser-1651426766418.jpg?v=1651426777" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0535/9088/4510/t/3/assets/use-heat-diffuser-1651426766418.jpg?v=1651426777 1536w" width="2245" height="1587" alt="Essential Oils using candle warmer or mug warmer" title="Mug warmer or candle warmer"/></div><p class="sc-fmBCVi laenLa pf-111_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jtXEFf kGfXVs pf-113_">If you don’t have the materials to make a simple reed diffuser, perhaps you have a mug warmer or candle warmer lying around. <br><br>If you do, then grab a jar or mug and simply follow the instructions for the reed diffuser, but no need to insert sticks or reeds. Place the jar or mug of carrier oil and essential oil on the mug warmer or candle warmer, and turn it on. As the warmer heats up, the oil will heat up and vaporize the essential oils, and you’ll begin to smell your amazing essential oil scents. <br><br>Of course, this method is less effective, but it will work in a pinch!</span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-9da1" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-bQtKYq fbyRgD pf-114_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-jHkVzv dyVEVs"><div class="sc-hiCibw hHrFfF pf-115_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hAcGzb bAQARH pf-116_"><div class="sc-hiCibw hHrFfF pf-117_ pf-r pf-c-cm" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hAcGzb bAQARH pf-118_"><div class="sc-hiCibw hHrFfF pf-119_ pf-r pf-c-cm" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hAcGzb bAQARH pf-120_"><div class="sc-hiCibw hHrFfF pf-121_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hAcGzb bAQARH pf-122_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-ctqQKy ioCblW pf-123_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jtXEFf kGfXVs pf-125_">Using a spray bottle as a diffuser</span></h3><div title="Using a spray bottle as a diffuser" data-pf-type="Image" class="sc-evcjhq dAUdgU pf-126_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0535/9088/4510/t/3/assets/essential-oil-spray-bottle-1651600095844.jpg?v=1651600106" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0535/9088/4510/t/3/assets/essential-oil-spray-bottle-1651600095844.jpg?v=1651600106 1536w" width="2245" height="1587" alt="flower essential oil in a spray bottle" title="Using a spray bottle as a diffuser"/></div><p class="sc-fmBCVi laenLa pf-127_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jtXEFf kGfXVs pf-129_">If a reed diffuser doesn’t feel like the right option for you and you don’t have a mug warmer or candle warmer, you may prefer to use a spray bottle to disperse your essential oils around your home.
<br><br>Simply add 25 drops of your favourite essential oils to a clean spray bottle. Then, add distilled water to the bottle, securely replace the lid and give it a shake. You can spritz this hydrosol on fabrics and furniture around your home with the peace of mind that it is safe and free from the harmful or toxic chemicals that are found in many aerosols and plug-in air fresheners.
<br><br>Many people enjoy spritzing their clothes with an awakening and uplifting essential oil in the morning to kickstart their day. Ideal oils for this include <a href="/products/grapefruit-essential-oil" target="_self">grapefruit essential oil</a> or <a href="/products/sweet-orange-essential-oil" target="_self">sweet orange essential oil</a>. On the other hand, you could also try <a href="/blogs/recipes/a-towel-freshener-that-smells-like-sea-breeze" target="_self">spritzing your pyjamas, towel or pillow</a> with a relaxing essential oil such as <a href="/products/lavender-essential-oil" target="_self">lavender</a> or <a href="/products/organic-roman-chamomile-essential-oil" target="_self">chamomile </a>before you settle down for the night. This can help you to relax and drift off to a deep, restful sleep.
<br><br>Whatever the time of day or occasion, there’s always a perfect essential oil to complement your mood and activities.
